column1: CONTENT:           CMIP5 RECOMMENDATIONS FOR ANNUAL AVERAGE, GLOBAL MEAN CONCENTRATIONS.
RCP4.5 CONTACT:    IMAGE group, Detlef van Vuuren (riahi@iiasa.ac.at)
FILE PRODUCED BY:  RCP Concentration Calculation & Data Group, M. Meinshausen, S. Smith, K. Riahi, D. van Vuuren
DOCUMENTATION:     M. Meinshausen, S. Smith et al. (2011) "The RCP GHG concentrations and their extension from 1765 to 2300", DOI 10.1007/s10584-011-0156-z, Climatic Change.
FURTHER INFO:      For data sources, aknowledgements and further information, see http://www.pik-potsdam.de/~mmalte/rcps.
NOTE:              RCP3PD starts 2005; 20th century data and earlier is provided for convenience.

1. CO2EQ            - (For Information only, not CMIP5 recommendation) CO2 equivalence concentrations using CO2 radiative forcing relationship Q = 3.71/ln(2)*ln(C/278), aggregating all (efficacy-adjusted) anthropogenic forcings, including greenhouse gases listed below (i.e. columns 3,4,5 and 8-35), and aerosols, trop. ozone etc. (not listed below).
2. KYOTO-CO2EQ      - (For information only, not CMIP5 recommendation) As column 1, but only aggregating greenhouse gases controlled under the Kyoto Protocol (columns 3,4,5 and 8-19).
6. FGASSUMHFC134AEQ - All flourinated gases controlled under the Kyoto Protocol, i.e. HFCs, PFCs, and SF6 (columns 8-19) expressed as HFC134a equivalence concentrations.
7. MHALOSUMCFC12EQ  - All flourinated gases controlled under the Montreal Protocol, i.e. CFCs, HCFCs, Halons, CCl4, CH3Br, CH3Cl (columns 20-35) expressed as CFC-12 equivalence concentrations.
8. - 19.            - Flourinated Gases controlled under the Kyoto Protocol
20. - 35.           - Ozone Depleting Substances controlled under the Montreal Protocol
